At least 161 people have been killed in a northeastern province of the DRC in the past week, local officials said on Monday, in an apparent resurgence of ethnic clashes between farming and herding communities. As Congolese continue to flee violence at "this massive scale", fears are that more people will try to seek safety in Uganda, crossing Lake Albert, UN High Commission for Refugees Spokesperson, Babar Baloch, told a news briefing in Geneva. --Reuters--